  "kind": "note",
  "title": "Easton: Peacock",
  "body": "(Heb. tuk, apparently borrowed from the Tamil tokei). This bird is indigenous to India. It was brought to Solomon by his ships from Tarshish (1 Kings 10:22; 2 Chr. 9:21), which in this case was probably a district on the Malabar coast of India, or in Ceylon. The word so rendered in Job 39:13 literally means wild, tumultuous crying, and properly denotes the female ostrich (q.v.).",
  "source": {
    "label": "Matthew Easton, Illustrated Bible Dictionary (1897)",
